1
00:01:04,146 --> 00:01:08,562
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:10,912
my day starts.

3
00:01:28,386 --> 00:01:33,058
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:33,058 --> 00:01:36,266
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:38,898 --> 00:01:40,585
PORK MISO COMBO, BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

6
00:01:40,585 --> 00:01:42,565
That's all I have on my menu.
PORK MISO COMBO, BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

7
00:01:42,711 --> 00:01:48,258
But I make whatever customers request,
as long as I have ingredients for it.

8
00:01:48,629 --> 00:01:50,712
That's my policy.

9
00:01:54,766 --> 00:01:56,558
Do I even have customers?

10
00:01:56,707 --> 00:01:58,999
More than you would expect.

11
00:02:01,058 --> 00:02:04,200
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

12
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:08,924
FRIED CHICKEN BREAST WITH CHEESE

13
00:02:51,558 --> 00:02:54,051
Let's go check it out.

14
00:02:54,051 --> 00:02:56,385
I'm not sure...

15
00:02:56,385 --> 00:02:58,980
Making plans for this weekend?

16
00:02:59,476 --> 00:03:03,226
They say there's a fortune-teller
at the east exit who is really good.

17
00:03:03,573 --> 00:03:05,359
The one in the alley?

18
00:03:05,359 --> 00:03:07,059
That's the one!

19
00:03:07,850 --> 00:03:10,683
-You know it?
-Yeah, I saw a line.

20
00:03:13,016 --> 00:03:15,683
Are you going to ask about marriage?

21
00:03:16,475 --> 00:03:18,516
What else?

22
00:03:18,652 --> 00:03:20,193
Here you go.

23
00:03:20,297 --> 00:03:22,380
-Chicken cheese katsu.
-Thanks.

24
00:03:23,817 --> 00:03:27,015
Do you believe in fortune-telling?

25
00:03:27,015 --> 00:03:29,689
Me? Whether I believe it or not,

26
00:03:29,689 --> 00:03:32,709
I think life turns out
however it turns out.

27
00:03:32,709 --> 00:03:33,876
I agree.

28
00:03:34,330 --> 00:03:36,268
It's never worked for me, anyway.

29
00:03:36,268 --> 00:03:40,155
I guess Mr. Chu will only believe it
when it comes to racehorses.

30
00:03:40,561 --> 00:03:43,003
I take it only as a reference.

31
00:03:43,003 --> 00:03:45,719
Many women like fortune-telling,
don't they?

32
00:03:46,131 --> 00:03:49,839
I don't believe all of it,
but I care about it a little.

33
00:03:50,722 --> 00:03:52,802
Like lucky items.

34
00:03:52,802 --> 00:03:56,093
I check my horoscope
on TV and in magazines, just in case.

35
00:03:58,176 --> 00:03:59,926
-And you, Mr. Yada?
-What?

36
00:04:00,999 --> 00:04:02,624
I would say...

37
00:04:03,246 --> 00:04:04,704
I believe it.

38
00:04:06,607 --> 00:04:11,065
Mr. Yada often orders
chicken cheese katsu here.

39
00:04:11,939 --> 00:04:17,231
He worked for an editing company,
and he is a writer as well.

40
00:04:23,516 --> 00:04:25,084
Welcome.

41
00:04:25,084 --> 00:04:27,167
Do you have chicken cheese katsu?

42
00:04:28,230 --> 00:04:31,342
Of course. In fact, I just made some.

43
00:04:31,342 --> 00:04:34,062
That's good to hear. Please.

44
00:04:34,062 --> 00:04:35,055
Sure.

45
00:04:37,243 --> 00:04:38,358
Hikaru!

46
00:04:38,358 --> 00:04:40,441
Are you an Aquarius, perhaps?

47
00:04:40,441 --> 00:04:41,358
Yes.

48
00:04:45,455 --> 00:04:48,455
Look, the Aquarius's lucky item!

49
00:04:50,183 --> 00:04:52,350
Chicken cheese katsu.

50
00:04:56,210 --> 00:05:00,193
Does that mean... You too, Mr. Yada?

51
00:05:01,409 --> 00:05:02,826
No, this is just...

52
00:05:05,051 --> 00:05:06,467
You found me out.

53
00:05:09,885 --> 00:05:12,510
AQUARIUS

54
00:05:14,056 --> 00:05:17,139
Most men don't read stuff like this.

55
00:05:17,773 --> 00:05:19,814
Our company subscribes to it.

56
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:23,707
I've been reading
that magazine since high school.

57
00:05:23,707 --> 00:05:26,999
Osanai sensei is amazing.
He always gets it right.

58
00:05:26,999 --> 00:05:29,501
Especially about love.

59
00:05:29,501 --> 00:05:30,821
That's true.

60
00:05:33,425 --> 00:05:37,300
Us two Aquarians coming together
must be fate.

61
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:38,383
It's nice to meet you.

62
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:40,964
You, too.

63
00:05:40,965 --> 00:05:43,715
Please come visit my bar if you like.

64
00:05:45,373 --> 00:05:46,331
Here.

65
00:05:49,737 --> 00:05:50,709
Hikaru.

66
00:06:07,677 --> 00:06:11,219
Mr. Yada! You really came!

67
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:18,392
-What is it?
-Nothing.

68
00:06:20,795 --> 00:06:23,087
-Here.
-You brought it?

69
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:26,428
-You've already read it?
-Of course.

70
00:06:26,428 --> 00:06:29,553
It says Aquarians
might have new encounters.

71
00:06:30,859 --> 00:06:32,567
-Whiskey and water?
-Please.

72
00:06:38,304 --> 00:06:42,679
You're a rare type,
being a man who likes astrology.

73
00:06:43,466 --> 00:06:45,216
It's not that I like it, but...

74
00:06:46,151 --> 00:06:50,318
There are times when someone
has no power over something, right?

75
00:06:51,318 --> 00:06:53,068
I like reading positive things.

76
00:06:53,941 --> 00:06:56,025
I know what you mean. I'm the same.

77
00:07:00,775 --> 00:07:02,483
-Here you are.
-Thank you.

78
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:12,484
Ever since I learned about
Osanai sensei when I was 17,

79
00:07:12,484 --> 00:07:17,747
I've always believed in him,
whether it was about work or love,

80
00:07:17,747 --> 00:07:19,747
whenever I was at a loss.

81
00:07:20,696 --> 00:07:22,029
I see.

82
00:07:22,884 --> 00:07:25,217
"New encounters."

83
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:27,319
I hope he's right.

84
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:32,707
Look.

85
00:07:32,707 --> 00:07:34,957
It says our lucky item is an apple pie.

86
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:39,527
-Do you know any nice shops?
-I should have brought one with me.

87
00:07:39,527 --> 00:07:41,267
You know a good place?

88
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:44,541
You could call it fate
guided by the fortune-telling.

89
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:49,573
Mr. Yada started to visit the club
to see Hikaru.

90
00:07:55,739 --> 00:07:58,848
What are you sighing about?

91
00:07:59,328 --> 00:08:01,896
I've been having some pain around here.

92
00:08:02,619 --> 00:08:05,286
-Heartburn?
-No, it's love.

93
00:08:06,576 --> 00:08:08,951
Many years have passed
since I've felt this.

94
00:08:09,694 --> 00:08:11,527
It's okay because I'm single, right?

95
00:08:12,503 --> 00:08:14,503
The lucky lady...

96
00:08:15,507 --> 00:08:17,632
could it be Hikaru?

97
00:08:20,606 --> 00:08:24,310
During the day,
she works for a design company.

98
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:27,481
She works as a part-time hostess
to pay off her student loan.

99
00:08:28,892 --> 00:08:31,684
I guess maybe she doesn't see me
as a love interest.

100
00:08:32,384 --> 00:08:35,501
What does the horoscope say about it?

101
00:08:35,943 --> 00:08:38,205
The star alignment isn't good now.

102
00:08:38,569 --> 00:08:43,879
Mars and Venus are close,
so Aquarian men need to be extra careful.

103
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:46,041
That's a shame.

104
00:08:47,414 --> 00:08:50,247
Besides, I'm no good
at making predictions for myself.

105
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:51,666
What?

106
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,833
To tell you the truth,
I write the horoscopes.

107
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,250
What?

108
00:09:00,009 --> 00:09:02,717
I learned how
when I wrote for an economics magazine.

109
00:09:03,916 --> 00:09:07,855
Many people working for big firms
believe in horoscopes,

110
00:09:07,855 --> 00:09:09,980
so I thought they could be an icebreaker.

111
00:09:10,917 --> 00:09:13,897
At some point,
I started writing in magazines sometimes

112
00:09:13,897 --> 00:09:15,772
under the name Kyoichiro Osanai.

113
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:18,482
I see.

114
00:09:19,154 --> 00:09:23,696
I haven't revealed my identity at all,
so no one knows it's me.

115
00:09:24,963 --> 00:09:27,838
Did you tell Hikaru about it?

116
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:30,370
Of course not.

117
00:09:30,797 --> 00:09:35,046
She'd be so disappointed if she learned
Osanai is a dull middle-aged man.

118
00:09:35,428 --> 00:09:36,678
So don't tell her, okay?

119
00:09:37,571 --> 00:09:38,488
All right.

120
00:09:41,842 --> 00:09:43,568
Good evening.

121
00:09:43,568 --> 00:09:45,768
-Hikaru!
-Mr. Yada.

122
00:09:45,768 --> 00:09:46,768
Welcome.

123
00:09:47,873 --> 00:09:50,873
This is Mr. Kikuchi,
a designer I'm working with.

124
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:53,544
-Beer?
-Sure.

125
00:09:53,544 --> 00:09:55,997
Beer and chicken cheese katsu, please.

126
00:09:56,363 --> 00:10:00,196
Excuse me.
Could you put in a few shiso leaves?

127
00:10:00,876 --> 00:10:02,902
-That's possible.
-Please.

128
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:03,735
Sure.

129
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:06,911
Mr. Kikuchi, how did you know?

130
00:10:06,911 --> 00:10:09,671
My lucky color this month is green!

131
00:10:09,671 --> 00:10:11,975
Is that so? It just came to me.

132
00:10:12,501 --> 00:10:14,167
Amazing!

133
00:10:17,475 --> 00:10:18,434
Mr. Yada.

134
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:22,000
I read that love is in the air
for Aquarians.

135
00:10:22,718 --> 00:10:23,843
It came true!

136
00:10:24,948 --> 00:10:26,323
Right?

137
00:10:47,879 --> 00:10:50,712
Two weeks passed.

138
00:10:53,606 --> 00:10:55,981
You're an Aquarius, right? Look.

139
00:10:56,795 --> 00:11:00,288
"Put a stop to last month's love.
The stars say it will soon end."

140
00:11:00,288 --> 00:11:02,121
No premonition, no presage.

141
00:11:03,631 --> 00:11:06,950
"Watch out for men's lies.
He might have a wife and children."

142
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:08,075
Not interested.

143
00:11:14,278 --> 00:11:15,403
Welcome.

144
00:11:16,681 --> 00:11:19,556
Hikaru! Long time no see.

145
00:11:23,883 --> 00:11:25,049
What's wrong?

146
00:11:25,991 --> 00:11:27,241
I was fooled.

147
00:11:29,701 --> 00:11:30,853
He...

148
00:11:30,853 --> 00:11:33,060
had a wife and a child.

149
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:34,580
-What?
-What?

150
00:11:34,580 --> 00:11:35,800
It's true!

151
00:11:42,156 --> 00:11:45,448
Of course it is. Because Mr. Yada...

152
00:11:46,311 --> 00:11:47,144
Here you go.

153
00:11:49,866 --> 00:11:52,491
That Kikuchi fella was no good.

154
00:11:53,241 --> 00:11:57,408
Not only was he married with a child,
he had women other than Hikaru!

155
00:11:57,991 --> 00:11:59,325
I see.

156
00:11:59,325 --> 00:12:01,698
You got all of that
from reading the stars?

157
00:12:01,698 --> 00:12:03,064
Of course not.

158
00:12:03,064 --> 00:12:08,763
After I met him that day,
I followed him home.

159
00:12:08,763 --> 00:12:11,304
Because I didn't like the look of him.

160
00:12:12,151 --> 00:12:14,943
Mr. Yada, you can read auras, too?

161
00:12:15,469 --> 00:12:16,602
You could say that.

162
00:12:16,981 --> 00:12:22,273
Since I'm a writer,
I looked into him enough to write a book.

163
00:12:27,429 --> 00:12:29,637
I questioned him
after reading the horoscope.

164
00:12:30,137 --> 00:12:34,345
He said, "I didn't deceive you.
I just didn't tell you the truth."

165
00:12:35,991 --> 00:12:38,924
What a jerk. That's terrible.

166
00:12:39,307 --> 00:12:44,099
But wasn't it better you found it out
before things went even further?

167
00:12:45,156 --> 00:12:45,990
Yeah.

168
00:12:47,718 --> 00:12:51,218
This Kyoichiro Osanai is too incredible,
by the way.

169
00:12:53,691 --> 00:12:56,483
I don't think I can
believe in anything anymore.

170
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:01,737
I might not be able to live
without the horoscope.

171
00:13:02,636 --> 00:13:06,656
Even after that,
Mr. Yada kept on using his horoscope

172
00:13:06,656 --> 00:13:11,333
to send messages to Hikaru
without revealing his true identity.

173
00:13:18,241 --> 00:13:21,950
People finish their day and hurry home.

174
00:13:22,517 --> 00:13:26,257
But sometimes
they don't want to go straight back home,

175
00:13:26,523 --> 00:13:29,064
so they drop in somewhere on the way home.

176
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:30,360
POLICE STATION

177
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:32,580
"As an Aquarius,

178
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:37,413
you are very thoughtful
and you think about things logically.

179
00:13:38,033 --> 00:13:42,700
But to those around you,
this can come off as indecisiveness."

180
00:13:43,187 --> 00:13:46,258
I guess it kind of fits me.

181
00:13:46,258 --> 00:13:50,019
That's right. You can come off
as thoughtless sometimes.

182
00:13:50,019 --> 00:13:51,819
-Really?
-Absolutely.

183
00:13:52,385 --> 00:13:53,551
Next is love.

184
00:13:54,336 --> 00:13:59,378
"You might realize that there is
someone close by who loves you."

185
00:14:15,358 --> 00:14:18,457
What's your sign, Ms. Izumi?

186
00:14:18,457 --> 00:14:22,158
-I'm a Virgo.
-No way. You must be a Cancer.

187
00:14:23,257 --> 00:14:24,091
Why?

188
00:14:24,091 --> 00:14:26,174
Because you're always so crabby.

189
00:14:27,757 --> 00:14:29,632
You're a Libra, right?

190
00:14:30,709 --> 00:14:31,709
Why?

191
00:14:32,699 --> 00:14:35,949
-Because you always sway.
-Sway...

192
00:14:37,441 --> 00:14:39,858
-Hi.
-Mr. Momi!

193
00:14:41,316 --> 00:14:43,108
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

194
00:14:43,108 --> 00:14:45,983
-Would you like some tea?
-No, thanks.

195
00:14:45,983 --> 00:14:49,152
We got a tip, so I went to check it out.

196
00:14:51,608 --> 00:14:54,233
-Horoscope?
-No, that's...

197
00:14:55,974 --> 00:14:58,058
The space is endlessly wide, right?

198
00:14:58,951 --> 00:15:01,326
So why are there only 12 zodiacs?

199
00:15:02,775 --> 00:15:04,150
That's a good question.

200
00:15:05,150 --> 00:15:08,191
Amazing! Great things are waiting for you!

201
00:15:13,609 --> 00:15:14,775
Excuse me.

202
00:15:18,424 --> 00:15:20,507
Can you look at mine?

203
00:15:21,463 --> 00:15:23,671
Everyone's doing it.

204
00:15:25,608 --> 00:15:30,150
Do fortune-tellers take responsibility
if they get things wrong?

205
00:15:32,778 --> 00:15:34,392
-I--
-What do you think?

206
00:15:34,392 --> 00:15:38,095
-I wonder...
-Let's see.

207
00:15:40,315 --> 00:15:44,781
DINER

208
00:15:47,984 --> 00:15:51,192
Are you three
dressed like a traffic light?

209
00:15:53,487 --> 00:15:57,174
How rude! These are our lucky love colors.

210
00:15:57,589 --> 00:15:59,048
Right?

211
00:16:00,441 --> 00:16:03,108
It's the real deal
if a man will approach you.

212
00:16:04,936 --> 00:16:07,353
By the way,
I haven't seen Hikaru these days.

213
00:16:08,076 --> 00:16:10,367
She hasn't been here for a while, either.

214
00:16:11,975 --> 00:16:14,100
It seems she stopped working as a hostess.

215
00:16:14,876 --> 00:16:17,310
Have you heard anything about her,
Mr. Yada?

216
00:16:17,745 --> 00:16:18,703
No.

217
00:16:20,683 --> 00:16:23,958
I wonder if she's still
heartbroken over the man.

218
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:25,976
She took it really hard.

219
00:16:25,976 --> 00:16:29,699
Yeah, she told us she couldn't
live without the horoscope.

220
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:32,271
She must have lost faith in herself.

221
00:16:32,768 --> 00:16:36,892
They say, "Happiness only comes to those
who are ready to accept it."

222
00:16:37,049 --> 00:16:38,049
Maybe...

223
00:16:38,525 --> 00:16:41,983
It's no good
if your fortune-teller is too accurate.

224
00:16:44,514 --> 00:16:47,056
Fortune-telling is hit or miss.

225
00:16:47,971 --> 00:16:49,369
When it comes to fortune-telling,

226
00:16:49,775 --> 00:16:52,483
it's best to take it
with a grain of salt, right?

227
00:17:01,435 --> 00:17:02,727
Thank you.

228
00:17:07,983 --> 00:17:09,775
-Where are you going?
-What?

229
00:17:23,453 --> 00:17:24,869
What should I do?

230
00:17:27,649 --> 00:17:28,607
About what?

231
00:17:29,305 --> 00:17:30,597
Hikaru.

232
00:17:31,876 --> 00:17:34,001
Did I do something wrong?

233
00:17:35,286 --> 00:17:36,411
Mr. Yada...

234
00:17:37,209 --> 00:17:40,000
You often order
chicken cheese katsu, right?

235
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:41,667
Yeah.

236
00:17:42,252 --> 00:17:43,043
Why?

237
00:17:43,595 --> 00:17:44,697
"Why"?

238
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:47,201
Because I like it.

239
00:17:47,736 --> 00:17:51,319
You eat it because you like it.
That's how things work, right?

240
00:17:52,647 --> 00:17:56,731
Why don't you try to be honest
about your feelings just once?

241
00:17:57,765 --> 00:17:59,390
Illogically.

242
00:18:09,741 --> 00:18:12,950
Two more weeks passed after that.

243
00:18:14,032 --> 00:18:15,824
"To the Aquarians.

244
00:18:16,475 --> 00:18:20,565
An important person of the opposite sex
will appear before you

245
00:18:20,565 --> 00:18:21,892
wearing a striped shirt.

246
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:25,081
This person may be your one true love."

247
00:18:25,081 --> 00:18:26,521
The striped shirt...

248
00:18:26,521 --> 00:18:30,237
Will it be blue stripes on white?
Or red stripes? What about the width?

249
00:18:35,909 --> 00:18:37,906
Hikaru! Long time no see!

250
00:18:38,599 --> 00:18:40,099
-Good evening.
-Welcome.

251
00:18:40,731 --> 00:18:42,627
Sorry I asked you out so suddenly.

252
00:18:42,943 --> 00:18:44,318
No, it's fine.

253
00:18:44,974 --> 00:18:47,144
Chicken cheese katsu for me, too, please.

254
00:18:47,401 --> 00:18:48,234
Sure.

255
00:18:51,957 --> 00:18:54,249
-What is it you wanted to talk about?
-Well...

256
00:18:54,983 --> 00:18:57,025
Have a drink, first.

257
00:18:57,214 --> 00:19:00,339
Who's this Kyoichiro Osanai, by the way?

258
00:19:00,870 --> 00:19:02,564
Is it only me thinking

259
00:19:02,564 --> 00:19:05,481
he's been especially focusing
on Aquarius recently?

260
00:19:05,481 --> 00:19:09,383
-That's true.
-But not one thing has come true for me.

261
00:19:09,383 --> 00:19:11,466
But it's been accurate for you, Hikaru?

262
00:19:14,025 --> 00:19:17,567
I'm okay. It's not the horoscope's fault.

263
00:19:18,454 --> 00:19:19,712
Sorry.

264
00:19:19,868 --> 00:19:21,772
I'm okay, really.

265
00:19:21,772 --> 00:19:23,365
Don't worry about me.

266
00:19:29,908 --> 00:19:30,991
Hikaru...

267
00:19:32,086 --> 00:19:33,961
you're perfect as you are.

268
00:19:34,866 --> 00:19:38,575
Aquarians tend to be too logical,
so you've got to be careful about it,

269
00:19:39,508 --> 00:19:41,686
but if you live,
being honest with your feelings,

270
00:19:41,686 --> 00:19:44,852
you'll surely meet someone
who loves you with all his heart.

271
00:19:45,626 --> 00:19:46,542
No...

272
00:19:47,146 --> 00:19:50,312
It could be that you've met one already,
but you just don't know it.

273
00:19:51,553 --> 00:19:52,595
Mr. Yada...

274
00:19:56,512 --> 00:19:57,698
Stripes!

275
00:19:58,283 --> 00:19:59,605
So, Hikaru, I...

276
00:20:00,138 --> 00:20:01,292
If you like, I want you to--

277
00:20:02,555 --> 00:20:03,578
Welcome.

278
00:20:04,366 --> 00:20:05,344
Stripes!

279
00:20:12,603 --> 00:20:14,222
Let's see...

280
00:20:14,608 --> 00:20:15,808
I'll have the pork soup set.

281
00:20:15,808 --> 00:20:17,132
Also, a beer.

282
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:18,368
Sure.

283
00:20:18,603 --> 00:20:19,520
Hikaru?

284
00:20:20,431 --> 00:20:21,390
Hikaru!

285
00:20:22,410 --> 00:20:24,980
Did you read the horoscope, perhaps?

286
00:20:26,018 --> 00:20:26,680
What?

287
00:20:27,396 --> 00:20:29,187
Why are you wearing stripes?

288
00:20:30,346 --> 00:20:34,847
My laundry hasn't dried yet,
and this is all I've got.

289
00:20:41,794 --> 00:20:43,503
It's fate!

290
00:20:44,066 --> 00:20:47,524
Kyoichiro Osanai's predictions
are really something else!

291
00:20:55,413 --> 00:20:56,455
Mr. Yada!

292
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:00,932
You shouldn't rely on horoscopes.

293
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:04,491
My lucky item has never done me any good,
not even once.

294
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:06,982
Let's get another drink.

295
00:21:34,917 --> 00:21:37,036
Wrap the cheese in the chicken breast,

296
00:21:37,036 --> 00:21:39,657
and cover it well
with batter and bread crumbs.

297
00:21:39,657 --> 00:21:44,407
Be careful the cheese doesn't melt
and leak out while frying.

298
00:21:45,491 --> 00:21:49,471
Try adding plums, cod roe,
or nori if you like.

299
00:21:49,471 --> 00:21:50,929
-Here you go.
-Thanks.

300
00:21:53,414 --> 00:21:54,498
Hikaru.

301
00:21:55,189 --> 00:21:58,106
The truth is,
I'm the one who writes the horoscope.

302
00:22:00,445 --> 00:22:02,487
I don't like liars.

303
00:22:07,777 --> 00:22:09,069
Good night.

304
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:47,386
THIS STORY IS A WORK OF FICTION

